<paragraph blockId="9.[189,927,1505,1534]" box="[189,927,1505,1534]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,927,1505,1534]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
Key to the 
<collectingCountry box="[330,477,1506,1534]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1826" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1826" box="[623,927,1505,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Drymeia Meigen, 1826</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="167" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1398,1557,1654]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
Males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2015" box="[301,721,1557,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cilitarsis">
<emphasis box="[301,441,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">D. cilitarsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C." box="[449,721,1557,1584]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" pagination="151 - 206" refId="ref7493" refString="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C. 2015. A review of the genus Drymeia Meigen, 1826 (Diptera: Muscidae) in Russia. Zootaxa 4000 (2): 151 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4000.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2015" box="[778,1184,1557,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[778,906,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">D. grandis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C." box="[913,1184,1557,1584]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" pagination="151 - 206" refId="ref7493" refString="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C. 2015. A review of the genus Drymeia Meigen, 1826 (Diptera: Muscidae) in Russia. Zootaxa 4000 (2): 151 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4000.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have not yet been found in 
<collectingCountry box="[293,431,1593,1619]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, but they are included in the key, since, according to the unidentified female, one of them may belong to the 
<collectingCountry box="[473,608,1628,1654]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[234,309,1693,1719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1693,1961]" box="[234,309,1693,1719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,309,1693,1719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">Males</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="168" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" type="key">
<key lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="168" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<keyStep pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1693,1961]" box="[189,1399,1728,1755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<keyLead box="[189,1399,1728,1755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">1. 3 pairs of postsutural dorsocentral setae ........................................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1693,1961]" box="[193,1399,1763,1790]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<keyLead box="[193,1399,1763,1790]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">– 4 pairs of postsutural dorsocentral setae ........................................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1693,1961]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
2. Mid femur curved, with 2 strong anteroventral setae on apical half, basal half of femur bare on anteroventral and posteroventral surfaces ............................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pont, 1975)" baseAuthorityName="Pont" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[1081,1398,1864,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valentinae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1081,1244,1864,1891]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">D. valentinae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pont A. C." box="[1260,1390,1864,1891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" pagination="136 - 139" refId="ref6811" refString="Pont A. C. 1975. Two new Muscidae (Diptera) from the Asiatic part of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 54: 191 - 196. [In Russian, with English summary. English translation in Entomological Review 54: 136 - 139.]" type="journal article" year="1975">Pont, 1975</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1693,1961]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="167">
– Mid femur with rows of anteroventral and posteroventral setae, strong setae absent ........................ ............................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Huckett, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Huckett" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1060,1398,1934,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Pogonomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firthiana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1060,1203,1934,1961]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="167">D. firthiana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Huckett H. C." box="[1219,1390,1934,1961]" pageId="9" pageNumber="167" pagination="1 - 370" refId="ref6594" refString="Huckett H. C. 1965. The Muscidae of Northern Canada, Alaska and Greenland (Diptera). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 42: 1 - 370. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 9742 fv" type="journal article" year="1965">Huckett, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[189,1399,265,291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead box="[189,1399,265,291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">3. Prealar seta strong. Mid tibia usually with 3–4 anterodorsal setae, rarely with 1–2 ........................ 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[193,1399,300,327]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead box="[193,1399,300,327]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">– Prealar seta absent. Mid tibia without or with 1–2 short anterodorsal setae .................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
4. Mid femur with anteroventral setae restricted to a group of 5–6 setae on apical fifth, and with a row of long posteroventral setae on basal ⅔ which at base are twice as long as diameter of femur. Hind femur without posteroventrals, only with fine posterior setae at base ... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stein, 1916)" baseAuthorityName="Stein" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[1068,1398,435,463]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Pogonomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciculata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1068,1237,435,462]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. fasciculata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stein P." box="[1254,1390,436,463]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 224" refId="ref7609" refString="Stein P. 1916. Die Anthomyiden Europas. Tabellen zur Bestimmung der Gattungen und aller mir bekannten Arten, nebst mehr oder weniger ausfuhrlichen Beschreibungen. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 81 A, 10 (1915): 1 - 224." type="journal article" year="1916">Stein, 1916</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
– Mid femur with rows of fine anteroventral and posteroventral setae, with fine and dense posterior to posteroventral setae which are as long as diameter of femur. Hind femur with a dense row of posteroventrals ........................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hennig, 1963)" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[976,1398,541,568]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Trichopticoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gymnophthalma">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[976,1212,541,568]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. gymnophthalma</emphasis>
(Hennig, 1963)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
5. Eye densely long-haired. Mid femur with a row of very long posteroventral setae, 2.3–2.5 × as long as diameter of femur. Black species ..................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2022" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2022" box="[1175,1301,642,669]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziegleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1175,1301,642,669]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. ziegleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1308,1399,643,669]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">– Eye bare or with very short hairs. Mid femur without or with only short, fine posteroventral setae. Grey species ...................................................................................................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
6. Anepimeron bare. Mid femur with a group of slender curved setae at extreme base of anteroventral surface and with 1–2 short ventral spinules on basal third .................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Huckett, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Huckett" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1067,1398,813,840]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Eupogonomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setibasis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1067,1205,813,840]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. setibasis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Huckett H. C." box="[1221,1390,813,840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 370" refId="ref6594" refString="Huckett H. C. 1965. The Muscidae of Northern Canada, Alaska and Greenland (Diptera). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 42: 1 - 370. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 9742 fv" type="journal article" year="1965">Huckett, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[193,1399,848,875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead box="[193,1399,848,875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">– Anepimeron setulose. Mid femur different ....................................................................................... 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
7. Tip of abdomen with a dense brush of slender black setae and setulae, caudally directed. Mid tibia without anterodorsals. Eye very short haired ............................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2015" box="[980,1399,949,976]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cilitarsis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[980,1120,949,976]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. cilitarsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C." box="[1128,1399,949,976]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" pagination="151 - 206" refId="ref7493" refString="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C. 2015. A review of the genus Drymeia Meigen, 1826 (Diptera: Muscidae) in Russia. Zootaxa 4000 (2): 151 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4000.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
– Tip of abdomen without such a brush of setae and setulae, at most with several caudally directed setulae on hypopygium. Mid tibia with 1–2 anterodorsals. Eye bare ...... 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2015" box="[992,1399,1019,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[992,1120,1019,1046]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. grandis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C." box="[1128,1399,1019,1046]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" pagination="151 - 206" refId="ref7493" refString="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C. 2015. A review of the genus Drymeia Meigen, 1826 (Diptera: Muscidae) in Russia. Zootaxa 4000 (2): 151 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4000.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="168" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[234,337,1085,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,337,1085,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">Females</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[189,1398,1120,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
The female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2022" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2022" box="[366,492,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziegleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[366,492,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. ziegleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[500,592,1121,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is not known, but we have included it in the key based on the male
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[190,317,1155,1181]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">characters.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" type="key">
<key lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="169" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[189,1399,1220,1247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead box="[189,1399,1220,1247]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">1. Prealar seta present and strong ......................................................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[193,1399,1254,1282]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead box="[193,1399,1254,1282]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
– Prealar seta absent or weak, shorter than 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[730,747,1254,1268]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">nd</superScript>
notopleural seta .......................................................... 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[189,1399,1320,1346]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead box="[189,1399,1320,1346]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">2. 4 postsutural dorsocentral setae; parafacial with an undusted shining patch near base of antenna .. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" box="[193,1399,1354,1381]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead box="[193,1399,1354,1381]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">– 3 postsutural dorsocentral setae; parafacial entirely dusted ............................................................. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
3. Arista appearing almost bare, the longest hairs shorter than its basal diameter; body grey, subshining; proboscis long, labella small; hind femur only with 1 weak posteroventral seta at base; fore tarsomere 5 normal, not flattened ........................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stein, 1916)" baseAuthorityName="Stein" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[1068,1398,1488,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Pogonomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciculata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1068,1237,1488,1515]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. fasciculata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stein P." box="[1254,1390,1489,1516]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 224" refId="ref7609" refString="Stein P. 1916. Die Anthomyiden Europas. Tabellen zur Bestimmung der Gattungen und aller mir bekannten Arten, nebst mehr oder weniger ausfuhrlichen Beschreibungen. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 81 A, 10 (1915): 1 - 224." type="journal article" year="1916">Stein, 1916</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
-– Arista pubescent, longest aristal hairs twice as long as its basal diameter; body black, shining; proboscis short and thick, labella large; hind femur with 1 weak posteroventral seta at base and with 2–3 posteroventral setae on basal third; fore tarsomere 5 moderately flattened ...................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hennig, 1963)" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[976,1398,1627,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Trichopticoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gymnophthalma">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[976,1212,1627,1654]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. gymnophthalma</emphasis>
(Hennig, 1963)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
4. Mid femur with 2anteroventrals on apical third, with 1anteroventral and 1posteroventral setae on basal third. Body brownish-grey dusted, sometimes with an olive tinge. Wing yellow at base. Lower facial margin projecting slightly forward beyond level of antennal base ........ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Huckett, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Huckett" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1062,1398,1761,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Pogonomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="firthiana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1062,1205,1761,1788]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. firthiana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Huckett H. C." box="[1221,1390,1761,1788]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 370" refId="ref6594" refString="Huckett H. C. 1965. The Muscidae of Northern Canada, Alaska and Greenland (Diptera). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 42: 1 - 370. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 9742 fv" type="journal article" year="1965">Huckett, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,265,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
<keyLead pageId="10" pageNumber="168">
– Mid femur only with 2 anteroventrals on apical third, otherwise without anteroventrals or posteroventrals. Body black, subshining. Wing black at base. Lower facial margin projecting well beyond level of antennal base .................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pont, 1975)" baseAuthorityName="Pont" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[1081,1398,1865,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valentinae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1081,1244,1865,1892]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="168">D. valentinae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pont A. C." box="[1260,1390,1865,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="168" pagination="136 - 139" refId="ref6811" refString="Pont A. C. 1975. Two new Muscidae (Diptera) from the Asiatic part of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 54: 191 - 196. [In Russian, with English summary. English translation in Entomological Review 54: 136 - 139.]" type="journal article" year="1975">Pont, 1975</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="11" pageNumber="169">
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1399,265,500]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">
<keyLead pageId="11" pageNumber="169">
5. Anepimeron setulose. Body whitish-grey dusted; thorax with 2–3 narrow brown vittae, sometimes indistinct. Lower facial margin not projecting slightly forward beyond level of antennal base. Mid femur with 1–2 fine anteroventrals on basal quarter .......................................................................... ........................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2015" box="[558,968,368,396]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[558,686,368,395]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">D. grandis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C." box="[694,968,369,396]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" pagination="151 - 206" refId="ref7493" refString="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C. 2015. A review of the genus Drymeia Meigen, 1826 (Diptera: Muscidae) in Russia. Zootaxa 4000 (2): 151 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4000.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2015" box="[980,1399,368,396]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cilitarsis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[980,1120,368,395]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">D. cilitarsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C." box="[1128,1399,369,396]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" pagination="151 - 206" refId="ref7493" refString="Sorokina V. S. &amp; Pont A. C. 2015. A review of the genus Drymeia Meigen, 1826 (Diptera: Muscidae) in Russia. Zootaxa 4000 (2): 151 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4000.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1399,265,500]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">
<keyLead pageId="11" pageNumber="169">
– Anepimeron bare. Body yellowish-grey dusted, with an olive tinge. Lower facial margin projecting slightly forward beyond level of antennal base. Mid femur with 3–4 strong anteroventrals on basal third ........................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Huckett, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Huckett" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1067,1398,472,500]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Eupogonomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setibasis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1067,1205,472,499]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">D. setibasis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Huckett H. C." box="[1221,1390,473,500]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" pagination="1 - 370" refId="ref6594" refString="Huckett H. C. 1965. The Muscidae of Northern Canada, Alaska and Greenland (Diptera). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada 42: 1 - 370. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 9742 fv" type="journal article" year="1965">Huckett, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
