<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="169" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,292,539,565]" box="[189,292,539,565]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,292,539,565]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,292,539,565]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">Remark</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1398,585,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">
The unknown female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sorokina &amp; Pont, 2022" authorityName="Sorokina &amp; Pont" authorityYear="2022" box="[482,609,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziegleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[482,609,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">D. ziegleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[616,708,585,611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
will probably key out to couplet 5 (with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Huckett" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1199,1338,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Eupogonomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setibasis">
<emphasis box="[1199,1338,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="169">D. setibasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and will be recognised by the very black body.
</paragraph>
